#Approach:

Move Zeroes – Two Pointer Approach

Sabse pehle array me first zero ka index find karo aur usse j pointer maan lo.
Agar zero mile hi na, to array already correct hai, return kar do.

Ab j ke baad traverse karo aur jab bhi non-zero element mile,
usse j index par swap karo aur j ko aage badha do.

Isse saare non-zero elements apni relative order me aage aa jayenge
aur saare zeroes automatically end me shift ho jayenge.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {

    private void swap(int[] nums, int a, int b){
        int temp = nums[a];
        nums[a] = nums[b];
        nums[b] = temp;
    }

    public void moveZeroes(int[] nums) {
        //Mark the first occuring zero
        int n = nums.length;
        int j = -1;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            if(nums[i] == 0){
                j = i;
                break;
            }
        }

        // if no zero present
        if(j == -1) return;


        //Now main logic of swapping begins
        for(int i = j+1; i<n; i++){
            if(nums[i] != 0){
                swap(nums, i, j);
                j++;
            }
        }
    }
}
